<task id="webhelp-change-toc-icons">
  <title>Changing the Icons in a WebHelp Table of Contents</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Customizing WebHelp Systems <indexterm>Customizing icons in the Table of
            Contents</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>You can change the icons that appear in a WebHelp table of contents by assigning new image
        files in a custom CSS file. By default, the icons for the WebHelp table of contents are
        defined with the following CSS codes (the first example is the icon that appears for a
        collapsed menu and the second for an expanded menu):
        <codeblock outputclass="language-css">.hasSubMenuClosed{
    background: url('../img/book_closed16.png') no-repeat;
    padding-left: 16px;
    cursor: pointer;
}</codeblock></p>
      <codeblock outputclass="language-css">.hasSubMenuOpened{
    background: url('../img/book_opened16.png') no-repeat;
    padding-left: 16px;
    cursor: pointer;
}</codeblock>
      <p>To assign other icons, use the following procedure:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Create a custom CSS file that assigns your desired icons to the
            <codeph>.hasSubMenuClosed</codeph> and <codeph>.hasSubMenuOpened</codeph> properties. </cmd>
        <stepxmp>
          <codeblock outputclass="language-css">.hasSubMenuClosed{
    background: url('TOC-my-closed-button.png') no-repeat;
}</codeblock>
          <codeblock outputclass="language-css">.hasSubMenuOpened{
    background: url('TOC-my-opened-button.png') no-repeat;
}</codeblock>
        </stepxmp>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/image-files-folder-ph"
          /></cmd>
        <substeps id="substeps_hc5_rjy_ls">
          <substep>
            <cmd><ph
                conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DITA-image-path-ph"
              /></cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd><ph
                conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DocBook-image-path-ph"
              /></cmd>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step id="specify-css-step">
        <cmd><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/transform-parameters-tab-ph"
          /></cmd>
        <substeps id="substeps_cjs_fj4_3r">
          <substep>
            <cmd><ph
                conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DITA-parameters-ph"
              /></cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd><ph
                conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DocBook-parameters-ph"
              /></cmd>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Run the transformation scenario.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
